main event: An unidentified oval-shaped object was observed over Alto, Tennessee on April 5, 1966.
interesting points: The object had a dull color when stationary but appeared brighter through the middle when moving.
A high frequency noise was heard coming from the object.
The object was sighted at three different locations and disappeared towards the south.
The object diminished in size to the size of a pin over the course of 2.5 hours.
The object moved erratically and irregularly, disturbing livestock in the area.
sighted object: an oval-shaped, dull colored object that became brighter through the middle when moving
photographs: no, the report indicates there were no photographs taken
